cheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 18287, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777582306360, \"responseId\": \"resp_06af1b7e5265ba5d0169f3c0e3469c819194a0055b0a0cca5c\"}}\n900:[tool-exec] start id=call_1GRlQgSFmwIiFL2DToUhIqoN|fc_06af1b7e5265ba5d0169f3c0f92ae081918fd4f29890b33fde name=write args={\"path\": \"tests/src/com.diffplug.spotless/spotless-lib/2.45.0/src/test/java/com_diffplug_spotless/spotless_lib/LazyForwardingEqualityTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_diffplug_spotless.spotless_lib;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\\nimport java.io.Serializable;\\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport com.diffplug.spotless.LazyForwardingEquality;\\n\\npublic class LazyForwardingEqualityTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void serializesAndDeserializesCalculatedState() throws Exception {\\n        CountingEquality.resetCalculations();\\n        final CountingEquality original = new CountingEquality(\\\"primary input\\\");\\n\\n        assertThat(CountingEquality.calculations()).isZero();\\n\\n        final byte[] serialized = serialize(original);\\n\\n        assertThat(CountingEquality.calculations()).isEqualTo(1);\\n\\n        final CountingEquality restored = deserialize(serialized);\\n\\n        assertThat(CountingEquality.calculations()).isEqualTo(1);\\n        assertThat(restored.toBytes()).isEqualTo(original.toBytes());\\n        assertThat(restored).isEqualTo(original);\\n        assertThat(restored.hashCode()).isEqualTo(original.hashCode());\\n        assertThat(CountingEquality.calculations()).isEqualTo(1);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static byte[] serialize(CountingEquality equality) throws Exception {\\n        final ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n        try (ObjectOutputStream outputStream = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\\n            outputStream.writeObject(equality);\\n        }\\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\\n    }\\n\\n    private static CountingEquality deserialize(byte[] serialized) throws Exception {\\n        try (ObjectInputStream inputStream = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(serialized))) {\\n            return (CountingEquality) inputStream.readObject();\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class CountingEquality extends LazyForwardingEquality<EqualityState> {\\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\\n        private static final AtomicInteger CALCULATIONS = new AtomicInteger();\\n\\n        private final String input;\\n\\n        private CountingEquality(String input) {\\n            this.input = input;\\n        }\\n\\n        private static void resetCalculations() {\\n            CALCULATIONS.set(0);\\n        }\\n\\n        private static int calculations() {\\n            return CALCULATIONS.get();\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        protected EqualityState calculateState() {\\n            CALCULATIONS.incrementAndGet();\\n            return new EqualityState(input.trim(), input.toUpperCase());\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class EqualityState implements Serializable {\\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\\n\\n        private final String normalized;\\n        private final String display;\\n\\n        private EqualityState(String normalized, String display) {\\n            this.normalized = normalized;\\n            this.display = display;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}\n905:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Designing serialization approach**\\n\\nI'm considering how to assert that serialization uses state without recalculating it on deserialization. If I have a lazy state that is transient, then my writeObject should capture the actual state, while readObject would then set that state. I'm contemplating if there's a need for a calculateState field. If the class has transient elements, I should design a SerializingEquality that extends LazyForwardingEquality with State. It's a bit complex but necessary!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_06af1b7e5265ba5d0169f3c0e431d8819196e80a1d1691e212\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp88D5sSDxNZfP9B7Va7pgAkd5WjyOadjPB_v4xsAp47JCar3rIEPKuY9XeMZY8t-Q8GZCPNy0mz-jBYtxevvhQnopSZX47XriG3CE7P9XnJkADU6xGNCKCtw-fAoRuA1VRxTI3OO7uc5Dyw1znvPqlqt0iO4KcM2Dya8-b-WND3uYfJVsj748lyn2mM54NpUETD0PHX1b9EjfQzEjmd0ss1URgXMbzSYQJIlQSNNTemBIgwWgByZyqJ5Q-qdIaK4V9HJBgXzY7hurD17OQnx545J_2oZzkvTQMUkI5qHiS_6WEig4ggOUDqTGpAZ3nSS9eT6E0Q4qMhsehNVCIAXMy80KSUeB1TVUPZeotbuN00o9i7KUWxvRtTNlr0aj_uyi6rgxar-19vP7qJWZZiAcCRcvROEda_TKs0PSBW1sLFmgcDV78fRtqcxqfVGNQkYC0Aj4k2y410Fnr7y_fri1-VffCv9USFCsdMZH5EhOoPk2tXW8ck0iFgfsocBwdb3M1mfHbcCmx2ScgnyqtS-0OSnyhf4SKO1Jcv1bCiPqhpbBryQ3TxnI34Jh-iU6WziinszMwUg1NsM-52uPC4hgDp-HsD1HNlj7CdIQmJQp6UDqQR1b6sCY_EXn2jKUpkmsyLDD0B_E-QfzGB5MhfiQcbACeeXiH0R3w_wv5V-w6m9QpreTfn4wQjCv3DNw_yZj--sRg9UiL_mNJBY3ploGzwomZdtJqDrqRgYBB3YfnjjXPEE0VmNi-woYimpm1WWgfIS99HVQL_L7Hc_yc9nJ-RaW2ZMe5BZHAhKAD20HNzC_WK97tCrqKv0KQU5wWfH_t1P5yp9pgLKk5ewA0eAem4r8PiZfzpTPGGI-aZyyaA05M3ERshgF0-mnzARc3cBKAZcjhyuNuYzDEE7krNbb2rdWvGfFm1vCp9OAGc48rvkJbK3fPqjEs8o-h5Mi783iMQTEOg12M-Tnw3f3YpHt8aS55E273iVDDnW2bdVVwCDj6KkJBJ4s6lg9Fb5fmlrvTLR_k8tsRSOb2KMfKJQWvGrjlXWfkJZqqvZcxbQTWx0P_5m6DmF6pwPJrwg76q48gkBIRqMC1AC0_FviMM_t8QI4uzZf5sSM4ua-sZAONAIc8SatxIG88IDVr_kTPrxMxQtjvDxUOZnAOdWGfmBt0pEhRLTdI7DNukJscBBwooIXMuyE-T4sIokZ-jHM1kaX3EBD7oYtuvS0upLqR_V9ZGyXllq